> When a hearty, colorful salad is just what you need, we've got you covered! You'll season and sizzle chickpeas and artichokes in a hot pan, then toss with leafy kale and fresh tomato in a quick homemade shallot and Dijon vinaigrette. Serve it with crispy, savory garlic bread to round out the meal.

Place @butter{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4 servings) in a small #microwave-safe bowl{}; bring to room temperature. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}. Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%oz}; chop into bite-size pieces. Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%400g can}; pat dry with paper towels. Roughly chop @artichoke hearts{1}. Dice @tomato{1} into 1⁄2-inch pieces.

In a second #small bowl{}, whisk together shallot, @red wine vinegar{5%tsp}, @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, @olive oil{3%tbsp}, and @sugar{1%tsp} (for 4 servings, use 6 TBSP olive oil and 2 tsp sugar). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Place kale in a large #bowl{} with a large drizzle of olive oil. Using your hands, massage kale (similar to how you would knead dough) until leaves are tender, about ~{1%minute}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chickpeas, artichokes, and @dried oregano{1%tsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until chickpeas and artichokes are tender and browned, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve and toast @ciabatta bread{1}.

Add @garlic powder{1%tsp} to bowl with softened butter; stir to combine.

> TIP: If needed, microwave butter in 30-second increments to soften.

Spread garlic butter onto cut sides of ciabatta. Cut each half into quarters.

To bowl with kale, add chickpeas and artichokes, tomato, and as much dressing as you like. Toss to combine.

Divide salad between shallow #bowls{} and serve with garlic bread on the side.